The paper discusses the development of a computer vision dataset for public safety scenarios, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a supercomputing cluster for efficient compute and storage, which could fall under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The dataset is also likely to involve issues related to security and privacy, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of intelligent organization techniques, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses large-scale inference across terabytes of data, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
